# CODEOWNERS makes the privileged CI trust boundary independently review-gated.
#
# GitHub requires a review from a listed owner before these paths can change on a
# branch-protected default branch. Combined with the workflows sourcing the privileged
# Bubblewrap helper from the immutable trusted base checkout, this ensures a pull request
# cannot alter what runs as root in CI (the helper, its pinned digest, the workflow logic,
# or this ownership rule itself) without an owner's review.
#
# NOTE: enforcement additionally requires branch protection with "Require review from Code
# Owners" enabled on the default branch. This file declares the intent in-repository.

# Default ownership for everything not matched below.
*                                        @TruPryce

# Privileged CI surface: workflows and the sudo-bearing sandbox helper.
/.github/workflows/                      @TruPryce
/.github/CODEOWNERS                      @TruPryce
/scripts/ci/                             @TruPryce
/scripts/ci/configure_bwrap_apparmor.sh  @TruPryce

# Immutable capability policy and adapters that gate agent execution.
/.ai/profiles/                           @TruPryce
/.ai/policies/                           @TruPryce
/.ai/providers/                          @TruPryce
/.ai/schemas/                            @TruPryce
/.ai/codex/                              @TruPryce
